<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Privacy Policy — AtimiScanner</title>
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --ink:      #1a1a1e;
      --ink-dim:  #555;
      --border:   #e2e2e7;
      --bg:       #f9f9fb;
      --accent:   #2563eb;
      --green:    #16a34a;
      --surface:  #fff;
    }

    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      :root {
        --ink:     #f0f0f5;
        --ink-dim: #9a9aaa;
        --border:  #2c2c36;
        --bg:      #111116;
        --surface: #1c1c24;
      }
    }

    body {
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', system-ui, sans-serif;
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.65;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    }

    .page {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 48px 24px 80px;
    }

    header {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding-bottom: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 36px;
    }

    .app-name {
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: .5px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ink-dim);
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 28px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -.3px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .meta {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--ink-dim);
    }

    /* Summary banner */
    .summary-box {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-left: 4px solid var(--green);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 20px 22px;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }
    .summary-box h2 {
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      color: var(--green);
    }
    .summary-box ul {
      list-style: none;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 7px;
    }
    .summary-box li {
      font-size: 15px;
      padding-left: 22px;
      position: relative;
    }
    .summary-box li::before {
      content: '✓';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--green);
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    /* Sections */
    section {
      margin-bottom: 36px;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      padding-top: 4px;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    ul.body-list {
      padding-left: 22px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }
    ul.body-list li {
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    /* Divider */
    hr {
      border: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      margin: 40px 0;
    }

    footer {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--ink-dim);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding-top: 24px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 480px) {
      h1 { font-size: 22px; }
      .page { padding: 32px 18px 60px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="page">

  <header>
    <div class="app-name">AtimiScanner</div>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">
      Effective date: <strong>June 17, 2026</strong> &nbsp;·&nbsp;
      Last updated: <strong>June 17, 2026</strong>
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- Plain-language summary up top -->
  <div class="summary-box">
    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AtimiScanner collects no personal data.</li>
      <li>Camera frames are processed on your device and never transmitted anywhere.</li>
      <li>There is no account, no login, and no user profile.</li>
      <li>There is no analytics SDK, no advertising SDK, and no crash reporter.</li>
      <li>AtimiScanner makes zero network requests — by design and by code.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <section id="who-we-are">
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner is a document and QR code scanner for iPhone, built and published
      by Jeff Griffith. Contact:
      <a href="mailto:grif.jef@gmail.com">grif.jef@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="what-we-collect">
    <h2>What data we collect</h2>
    <p><strong>None.</strong></p>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data.
      It does not create a user account, assign a device identifier, or maintain
      any persistent record that identifies you.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="camera">
    <h2>Camera access</h2>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner requests access to your iPhone's camera solely to display a
      live viewfinder for scanning documents and QR codes. Camera frames are
      processed entirely on your device using on-device JavaScript running inside
      a WebKit web view. No camera frame, captured image, or scanned document
      is transmitted to any server, cloud service, or third party.
    </p>
    <p>
      Images are stored in memory only for the duration of your active scan session.
      When you close the app, all in-memory data is discarded. AtimiScanner never
      writes to your photo library unless you explicitly use the iOS share sheet
      to save a file there yourself.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="qr-codes">
    <h2>QR code and barcode scanning</h2>
    <p>
      When you scan a QR code, the decoded content (a URL, Wi-Fi credential,
      contact card, calendar event, or plain text) is displayed on screen and
      used to populate an action sheet. This content is never logged, stored
      beyond the current session, or sent anywhere.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you choose to <em>open a URL in Safari</em>, that action is handled by
      iOS and is subject to Apple's own privacy practices. AtimiScanner itself
      makes no network request in connection with QR results.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="no-network">
    <h2>Network requests</h2>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner is engineered to make zero network requests. The app enforces a
      strict Content Security Policy (CSP) inside the web view that explicitly
      blocks <code>connect-src</code>, preventing all outbound HTTP, WebSocket,
      and fetch connections. The Swift host layer contains no
      <code>URLSession</code> or <code>URLRequest</code> calls.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is verifiable: AtimiScanner's source code is open to inspection and
      the network prohibition is enforced at runtime by the browser engine, not
      merely by policy.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="third-parties">
    <h2>Third-party SDKs and services</h2>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner contains no third-party code of any kind. It uses only Apple's
      built-in frameworks:
    </p>
    <ul class="body-list">
      <li><strong>WebKit</strong> — hosts the scanner UI inside a WKWebView</li>
      <li><strong>UIKit</strong> — provides the native iOS app shell and share sheet</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      There is no analytics library (no Firebase, no Mixpanel, no Amplitude).
      There is no advertising SDK (no AdMob, no Meta Audience Network).
      There is no crash-reporting SDK (no Crashlytics, no Sentry).
      Apple's built-in crash logging via iOS may record anonymized crash data
      if you have opted in to sharing diagnostics with Apple — this is Apple's
      system, controlled in iOS Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Analytics &amp;
      Improvements, and is outside AtimiScanner's scope entirely.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="pdf-export">
    <h2>PDF export and sharing</h2>
    <p>
      When you tap <em>Export PDF</em>, a PDF is assembled on your device from
      your scanned images using a JavaScript-based PDF writer. The resulting
      file is written to a temporary location in your device's local storage
      and offered to you via the iOS share sheet.
    </p>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner does not retain a copy of exported PDFs after the share
      sheet is dismissed. Temporary files are stored in <code>NSTemporaryDirectory()</code>
      and are cleared by iOS at its discretion.
    </p>
    <p>
      Where a PDF ends up after you share it (Files, Mail, AirDrop, a third-party
      app) is governed by that destination's own privacy practices. AtimiScanner
      has no visibility into or control over the destination.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="children">
    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner does not collect data from anyone, including children under
      the age of 13. The app is rated 4+ on the App Store.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="changes">
    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted at this URL with
      a revised <em>Last updated</em> date. Because AtimiScanner collects no data,
      we do not need to notify you of changes — but we will keep this page current
      in the interest of transparency.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="contact">
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy or AtimiScanner's privacy practices can be
      sent to <a href="mailto:grif.jef@gmail.com">grif.jef@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Bug reports and feature requests:
      <a href="https://github.com/grifjef/atimiscanner/issues">github.com/grifjef/atimiscanner/issues</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr>

  <footer>
    <p>
      AtimiScanner · Privacy Policy · Effective June 17, 2026<br>
      <a href="mailto:grif.jef@gmail.com">grif.jef@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </footer>

</div>
</body>
</html>
